            <h2 class="mt-4">Why GeoBlazor?</h2>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>Declarative Syntax</h4>
                    <p>
                        Build maps using familiar Razor component syntax instead of imperative JavaScript.
                        Your map configuration becomes part of your component tree.
                    </p>
                    <pre><code>&lt;MapView Latitude="34.027" Longitude="-118.805" Zoom="12"&gt;
    &lt;Map&gt;
        &lt;Basemap&gt;
            &lt;BasemapStyle Name="BasemapStyleName.ArcgisStreets" /&gt;
        &lt;/Basemap&gt;
    &lt;/Map&gt;
&lt;/MapView&gt;</code></pre>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>Type Safety</h4>
                    <p>
                        Full C# type safety with IntelliSense support. No more runtime errors from typos
                        in string-based configuration.
                    </p>
                    <pre><code>// Strongly-typed event handling
private Task OnMapClick(ClickEvent e)
{
    var lat = e.MapPoint?.Latitude;
    var lng = e.MapPoint?.Longitude;
    // Full IntelliSense support!
    return Task.CompletedTask;
}</code></pre>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row mt-3">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>Rich Ecosystem</h4>
                    <p>
                        Access the full power of ArcGIS Maps SDK including advanced analysis, geocoding,
                        routing, and thousands of ready-to-use basemaps and data layers.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h4>.NET Integration</h4>
                    <p>
                        Seamless integration with ASP.NET Core, Entity Framework, and the entire .NET ecosystem.
                        Use your existing skills and tools.
                    </p>
                </div>
